                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18240114-25-victim308 t18240114-25-viclabel144"></join>; this fender was in the entrance passage to the shop. I missed it in consequence of information; ran out and stopped the prisoner in Pater-noster-row, with the fender on his shoulder, and told him it was not his; he said,</p>

               <p>"If it is your's, take it." I took it from him; he gave me a push into the road, and ran off, but was stopped without my losing sight of him.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. Two men employed me to take it to Little Britain. I asked them to tie my hands, and let me go to Little Britain.</p>
